                    <div class="comment-content content">
                        <p>The title, &#8220;Gaussian distributions are monoids&#8221; makes it sound like each individual Gaussian distribution is a monoid (which is nonsense and is the reason I clicked through to see what the heck was going on). I think you meant something like &#8220;Gaussian distributions form a monoid&#8221;, or more precisely that the type &#8220;Gaussian a&#8221; in your library is a monoid. To make this clear consider &#8220;The natural numbers form a monoid&#8221; vs &#8220;Natural numbers are monoids&#8221;.</p>
                    </div>
                    
