        <li class="comment odd alt depth-5 comment-lvl-first" id="comment-982">
            <div class="comment-wrapper clearfix" id="comment-wrapper-982">
                                                        
                    <img alt="Michael Thompson&#8217;s avatar" src="http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/2016159480607b2c079bb70df33c3bae?s=50&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D50&amp;r=G" class="avatar avatar-50 photo"  />                    
                    <p class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><span class="comment-author vcard"><span class="fn">Michael Thompson</span></span> on <span class="comment-permalink"><a title="Permalink to this comment" href="http://izbicki.me/blog/gausian-distributions-are-monoids#comment-982">November 26, 2012 at 10:03 AM</a></span>                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="comment-content content">
                        <p>The haddocks for version 0.2 <a href="https://github.com/liyang/vector-th-unbox/issues/2" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-comment','http://github.com']);" rel="nofollow">subtly wrong</a> It seems the new incantation should be:</p>
<p><code><br />
derivingUnbox "Gaussian"<br />
    [t| (U.Unbox a) =&gt;  (Gaussian a) -&gt; (Int, a, a, Int) |]<br />
     [| \ (Gaussian n m1 m2 dc) -&gt; (n,m1,m2,dc) |]<br />
     [| \ (n,m1,m2,dc) -&gt; (Gaussian n m1 m2 dc) |]<br />
</code></p>
<p>note the &#8216;t&#8217; in place of &#8216;d&#8217;.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                                                </div>
